09/08/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- A bridegroom in southeast Gaziantep province accidentally killed three of his relatives at his own wedding Sunday (August 8th).
The groom was firing an AK-47 in the air, a traditional custom during Turkish weddings, when he lost control of the gun and wounded eight people.
Three of them -- his father and two aunts -- succumbed to their injuries later in hospital.
The groom has been arrested.
(BBC, Hurriyet, AP - 08/08/10)
